steps.description:
First, strip the orange wire on both cut sides down. (approx. 1/4 or 1/2 inch){"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/7a/Make-a-Crossover-Cable-from-One-Standard-Ethernet-Cable-Step-5Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Crossover-Cable-from-One-Standard-Ethernet-Cable-Step-5Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/7a/Make-a-Crossover-Cable-from-One-Standard-Ethernet-Cable-Step-5Bullet1.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Crossover-Cable-from-One-Standard-Ethernet-Cable-Step-5Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":334,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":552.2527472527472,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

After both ends of the orange wire has been stripped, strip both ends of the green wire down. (approx. 1/4 or 1/2 inch){"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/ed/Make-a-Crossover-Cable-from-One-Standard-Ethernet-Cable-Step-5Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Crossover-Cable-from-One-Standard-Ethernet-Cable-Step-5Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/ed/Make-a-Crossover-Cable-from-One-Standard-Ethernet-Cable-Step-5Bullet2.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Crossover-Cable-from-One-Standard-Ethernet-Cable-Step-5Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":334,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":552.2527472527472,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Start by stripping the green-white wires. (once again, approx. 1/4 or 1/2 inch){"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/56/Make-a-Crossover-Cable-from-One-Standard-Ethernet-Cable-Step-8Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Crossover-Cable-from-One-Standard-Ethernet-Cable-Step-8Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/56/Make-a-Crossover-Cable-from-One-Standard-Ethernet-Cable-Step-8Bullet1.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Crossover-Cable-from-One-Standard-Ethernet-Cable-Step-8Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":334,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":552.2527472527472,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Repeat the wire stripping on orange-white wires. (once again, approx. 1/4 or 1/2 inch){"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/3f/Make-a-Crossover-Cable-from-One-Standard-Ethernet-Cable-Step-8Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Crossover-Cable-from-One-Standard-Ethernet-Cable-Step-8Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/3f/Make-a-Crossover-Cable-from-One-Standard-Ethernet-Cable-Step-8Bullet2.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Crossover-Cable-from-One-Standard-Ethernet-Cable-Step-8Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":334,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":552.2527472527472,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Note the direction that the wiring in the cable case is twisting. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/02/Make-a-Crossover-Cable-from-One-Standard-Ethernet-Cable-Step-11Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Crossover-Cable-from-One-Standard-Ethernet-Cable-Step-11Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/02/Make-a-Crossover-Cable-from-One-Standard-Ethernet-Cable-Step-11Bullet1.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Crossover-Cable-from-One-Standard-Ethernet-Cable-Step-11Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":334,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":552.2527472527472,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Holding the cable in your hands, twist the cable in the same way as the internal wiring is twisted. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/43/Make-a-Crossover-Cable-from-One-Standard-Ethernet-Cable-Step-11Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Crossover-Cable-from-One-Standard-Ethernet-Cable-Step-11Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/43/Make-a-Crossover-Cable-from-One-Standard-Ethernet-Cable-Step-11Bullet2.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Crossover-Cable-from-One-Standard-Ethernet-Cable-Step-11Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":334,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":552.2527472527472,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Keep the wire twisted, and close it up with tape or shrink-wrap. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/bf/Make-a-Crossover-Cable-from-One-Standard-Ethernet-Cable-Step-11Bullet3.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Crossover-Cable-from-One-Standard-Ethernet-Cable-Step-11Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/bf/Make-a-Crossover-Cable-from-One-Standard-Ethernet-Cable-Step-11Bullet3.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Crossover-Cable-from-One-Standard-Ethernet-Cable-Step-11Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":334,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":552.2527472527472,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}
